      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>This collection consists of the additional papers of the
         American author, book reviewer, and George Mason University
         professor, Alan Cheuse, ca. 3,200 items (10 Hollinger boxes,
         ca. 4 linear shelf feet), ca. 1971-1998. These papers include
         manuscripts for articles, speeches, interviews, and short
         stories; book reviews, both published and for 
         <title render="italic">All Things Considered</title>on
         National Public Radio; screen plays; cassette tape recordings,
         computer disks, and a video cassette "Carlos Fuentes: Man of
         Two Worlds;" printed material; contracts and royalties;
         passports; photographs and drawings; correspondence; research
         material; short stories by other authors; appointment
         calendars; short stories used in 
         <title render="italic">The Sound of Writing</title>; and a
         collection of short stories assembled for publication as 
         <title render="italic">Lost and Old Rivers</title>. Other book
         manuscripts include 
         <title render="italic">The Light Possessed</title>and 
         <title render="italic">On Earth as It Is</title>.</p>
      </scopecontent>
